<DOC><DOCNO>WSJ910521-0106</DOCNO><DOCID>910521-0106.</DOCID><HL>   Adobe Systems Inc.</HL><DATE>05/21/91</DATE><SO>WALL STREET JOURNAL (J), PAGE A8</SO><CO>   ADBE LOTS MSFT</CO><MS>TECHNOLOGY (TEC)</MS><IN>SOFTWARE (SOF)</IN><RE>CALIFORNIA (CA)MASSACHUSETTS (MA)WASHINGTON (WA)</RE><LP>   MOUNTAIN VIEW, Calif. -- Adobe Systems Inc. said it agreedto allow Lotus Development Corp. to use Adobe's typefacesoftware in all Lotus software. The deal solidifies Adobe'sdominance in the market for &quot;font&quot; software that controls howtypefaces are created by printers and displayed on computerscreens.   Under the agreement, Adobe will allow Lotus, Cambridge,Mass., to use Adobe's Type Manager software in all of Lotus'ssoftware. Lotus will first use the software, which, amongother things, smooths out the jagged lines in on-screencharacters, on a version of Lotus's popular 1-2-3 spreadsheetprogram written to run on Microsoft Corp.'s Windows software,Adobe said.</LP><TEXT/></DOC>